---
title: "Dialectical Protocol — Sequence Flow"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Q as Query/Context
    participant RL as RL Retrieval Agent
    participant KG as Knowledge Hypergraph
    participant T as Thesis Agents (α,β,γ)
    participant A as Antithesis Agents
    participant CT as Contradiction Trackers
    participant S as Synthesis Agents (α,β)
    participant M as Meta-Reflection
    participant SI as Schema Induction

    Q->>RL: New decision context
    RL->>KG: Think → Query → Retrieve subgraph
    KG-->>RL: Concept neighborhood + alive claims + open contradictions
    RL->>T: Retrieved context + prior contradictions

    rect rgb(26, 21, 16)
        Note over T,A: Phase 1-2: Thesis Generation & Cross-Negation
        T->>T: Generate 2-5 competing framings<br/>(heterogeneous models)
        T->>KG: Write concept subgraphs + claims + regime assumptions
        T->>A: Each thesis exposes: categories, causal model, falsification criteria
        A->>A: Structured negation per thesis
        A->>KG: Write contradicts edges + category error annotations
        A-->>T: "Your concept X conflates Y and Z"<br/>"Causal arrow reverses under regime R"
    end

    rect rgb(26, 16, 16)
        Note over CT: Phase 3: Contradiction Crystallization
        CT->>KG: Query all active contradiction edges
        CT->>CT: LogicTracker: A ∧ ¬A patterns
        CT->>CT: PragmaticTracker: action-incompatible claims
        CT->>CT: SemanticTracker: concept equivocation
        CT->>CT: BoundaryTracker: regime mismatch
        CT->>CT: Cross-verification round
        CT->>KG: Write ranked contradiction nodes<br/>with action_distance scores
        CT-->>S: Minimal inconsistent set (MIS)
    end

    rect rgb(16, 26, 16)
        Note over S,SI: Phase 4: Sublation (Aufhebung)
        S->>S: Synthesizer α (parsimony) produces graph rewrites
        S->>S: Synthesizer β (scope) produces graph rewrites
        S->>S: Cross-negation of competing syntheses
        S->>KG: Execute typed rewrite operators:<br/>SPLIT | MERGE | REVERSE_EDGE |<br/>ADD_MEDIATOR | SCOPE_TO_REGIME | TEMPORALIZE
        S->>KG: Write supersedes edges + new claims
        SI->>KG: Schema induction: auto-cluster new concepts<br/>Version ontology layer
    end

    rect rgb(26, 16, 26)
        Note over M: Phase 5-6: Re-grounding & Meta-Reflection
        S->>KG: New predictions with timestamps + test criteria
        M->>KG: Check conceptual velocity (category ops per cycle)
        M->>M: Stuck loop? Premature collapse?<br/>Epistemic vs ontic confusion?

        alt Velocity > threshold
            M-->>T: Continue: new thesis from sublated output
        else Velocity flatlined 2+ cycles
            M-->>Q: Terminate: output regime-scoped policies
        else Stuck in binary oscillation
            M-->>T: Re-specify: change unit of analysis<br/>or abstraction level
        end
    end

    Note over KG: RL reward computed:<br/>R = α·contradiction_reduction +<br/>β·prediction_accuracy + γ·concept_parsimony
    KG-->>RL: Reward signal → update retrieval policy
